To visualize the distribution of the Sales data, we can create a histogram. This will help us understand the frequency of sales amounts within specific ranges.

Let's generate a histogram using the Sales column:

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Plotting a histogram for the Sales column
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.histplot(data=df, x='Sales', bins=10, kde=True, color='blue')
plt.title('Distribution of Sales')
plt.xlabel('Sales')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

This code will create a histogram with 10 bins and overlay a kernel density estimate (KDE) to give a smoother view of the distribution. The x-axis represents the sales amounts, while the y-axis represents the frequency of these amounts occurring in the dataset.
